Send File Notifications from External Blob Stores to Data Cloud

Create file notification pipelines from your cloud provider to notify a Salesforce connected app whenever unstructured data files are added, updated, or deleted from your external blob store. File notifications are the only way by which Data Cloud picks up new or updated files from an external blob store.

You can create file notification pipelines for Amazon S3, Google Cloud Platform Storage, and Microsoft Azure Blob Storage.

Send File Notifications from Amazon S3 to Data Cloud
Create a file notification pipeline for Amazon S3 to notify a Salesforce connected app whenever unstructured data files are added, updated, or deleted from a bucket.
Send File Notifications from Google Cloud Storage to Data Cloud
Create a file notification pipeline for Google Cloud Platform (GCP) Storage to notify a Salesforce connected app whenever unstructured data files are added, updated, or deleted from a bucket.
Send File Notifications from Azure Blob Storage to Data Cloud
Create a file notification pipeline for Microsoft Azure Blob Storage to notify a Salesforce connected app whenever unstructured data files are added, updated, or deleted from a bucket.
